    <note>Cai(1) Kang [1653] Ting's [1661] elder brother, Zheng's [3856] brother, and Meng's [1654] Yu(1)'s [1663] Tianqiu's [7069] and Tianshen's [1660] uncle. Zhang(1) Wenzhi's [318] son-in-law and  Zeng(1) Xiaoxu's [1694] father-in-law. A son, Qin [3851], died at the age of nineteen before he was married. His grandnephew, Fan [3857], used Kang's yin to enter the civil service. Fan's two sons were recommended for the exams by the local community, at the same time (xiangjian). Fan's son-in-law, Liu(2) Changli [3582], has the same generational name as the grandsons of Liu(2) Zhi [8089], whose son, Liu(2) Qi [3583], is the author of Fan's funerary inscription. Zhang Fangping, WJ, 40.11b; Zhu Changwen, WJ, 10.3a; XCB, 197.14b; Guangdong TZ, 14.26a; Liu Qi, WJ, 8.95; SS, 328.17a-17b; Wang Anshi, WJ, 52.556. CBD, 5, 3783-4.</note>
